main event: On December 22, 1967, an observer in Honaker, Virginia reported seeing a stationary object with bright flashing lights in the sky.
interesting points: The object was described as having various colored lights on its bottom., The observer indicated the sighting lasted approximately 2 minutes., There was no sound associated with the object., The conclusion of the investigation stated there was insufficient data to evaluate the sighting., The report details a discrepancy in the record's date and time entries.
sighted object: stationary object with bright flashing lights
witness description: A civilian observer who noticed the object from the ground.
